{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e78528c1-c336-452f-8a67-2b45109847a3","content":"The directory doesn't exist yet, but I can tell you exactly what you need to configure in your `.csproj` to publish as a dotnet tool:\n\n### Required `.csproj` properties\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <!-- Makes it a dotnet tool -->\n  <PackAsTool>true</PackAsTool>\n\n  <!-- The command users will run (e.g., `dotnet tool install -g my-mcp-server`) -->\n  <ToolCommandName>my-mcp-server</ToolCommandName>\n\n  <!-- Must be Exe for stdio transport -->\n  <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n\n  <!-- NuGet metadata -->\n  <PackageId>MyMcpServer</PackageId>\n  <Version>1.0.0</Version>\n  <Authors>YourName</Authors>\n  <Description>An MCP server for …</Description>\n  <PackageProjectUrl>https://github.com/you/MyMcpServer</PackageProjectUrl>\n  <PackageLicenseExpression>MIT</PackageLicenseExpression>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n### Publish steps\n\n```bash\n# 1. Pack\ndotnet pack -c Release\n\n# 2. Push to NuGet.org (get an API key from nuget.org/account/apikeys)\ndotnet nuget push bin/Release/MyMcpServer.1.0.0.nupkg \\\n  --api-key YOUR_API_KEY \\\n  --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\n### Users install & run it with\n\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g MyMcpServer\nmy-mcp-server          # runs via stdio\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- `PackAsTool` + `OutputType=Exe` are the critical settings.\n- `ToolCommandName` controls the CLI command name (defaults to the assembly name if omitted).\n- The tool automatically works with stdio since it's just a console app.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"bd4447b1-a3de-499d-9d99-f5388568e9a3","outputTokens":477,"requestId":"700B:1D248C:1501E83:183862F:69EC11EA"},"id":"c81a64c9-cc36-4b29-afbc-22270c00ff6a","timestamp":"2026-04-25T00:59:31.999Z","parentId":"bb15dba4-d44a-4481-9718-2fc74cddb0df"}
